      <constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>&lt;pre&gt;[Congressional Record Volume 169, Number 130 (Thursday, July 27, 2023)][House]From the Congressional Record Online through the Government Publishing Office [&lt;a href="https://www.gpo.gov"&gt;www.gpo.gov&lt;/a&gt;]By Ms. MOORE of Wisconsin:H.R. 5028.Congress has the power to enact this legislation pursuantto the following:Article I, Section 8, Taxing and Spending ClauseThe single subject of this legislation is:This bill would ensure that federal funds provided tosupport state child protective service systems are not beinginappropriately used to separate children from their parentssolely due to poverty.[Page H4145]&lt;/pre&gt;</constitutionalAuthorityStatementText>
